Text.LocalizedString: No combat this weekend?

Text.SourceString: Vacationing?
Text.LocalizedString: Vacationing?

Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to learn how to stretch correctly. <NPCName>Leah’s</> learning from videos on the internet.//<portrait=happy>You heard about those?

Text.SourceString: I’m going to buy the videos and do them at home. That way, I don’t need to come here.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to buy the videos and do them at home. That way, I don’t need to come here.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to succeed in combat if you’re not coordinated.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to succeed in combat if you’re not coordinated.

Text.SourceString: You got it, <PlayerName>$player</>! And I don’t say that lightly. Keep it up!
Text.LocalizedString: You got it, <PlayerName>$player</>! And I don’t say that lightly. Keep it up!

Text.SourceString: I have to dig out some of my old blades one of these days.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to dig out some of my old blades one of these days.

Text.SourceString: Clean off the rust, sell them. I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: Clean off the rust, sell them. I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: It’s impossible to live alone without people bothering you, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s impossible to live alone without people bothering you, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Fodder? Food for animals? No, I don’t have any.//You’ve come to the wrong place.
Text.LocalizedString: Fodder? Food for animals? No, I don’t have any.//You’ve come to the wrong place.

Text.SourceString: Up there, see the barns? You can buy it there. You passed the building already.//<portrait=happy>Also, I’d go and see <NPCName>Charlie</> if I were you. Might need to have that disorientation checked out.
Text.LocalizedString: Up there, see the barns? You can buy it there. You passed the building already.//<portrait=happy>Also, I’d go and see <NPCName>Charlie</> if I were you. Might need to have that disorientation checked out.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Charles</>? Yeah, that’s what I said.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Charles</>? Yeah, that’s what I said.

Text.LocalizedString: You can try using your farming tools to fight monsters, but I don’t know how far it’ll get ya.

Text.SourceString: Check out my list over there. I’ll give you rewards for slaying certain monsters.
Text.LocalizedString: Check out my list over there. I’ll give you rewards for slaying certain monsters.

Text.SourceString: Bring me the monsters first. Okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Bring me the monsters first. Okay?

Text.LocalizedString: The barn’s kind of a mess. It hasn’t been lived in for years.//<NPCName>Jack</> used to live there before we got married. It’s falling apart now.

Text.SourceString: It’s been empty ever since. Cobwebs. Rats. Gah.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been empty ever since. Cobwebs. Rats. Gah.

Text.LocalizedString: I’m here for a routine checkup. How else am I going to keep healthy?

Text.SourceString: These folks seem to know what they’re talking about.//Especially <NPCName>Charlie</>. I like him. He’s the straightforward type.
Text.LocalizedString: These folks seem to know what they’re talking about.//Especially <NPCName>Charlie</>. I like him. He’s the straightforward type.

Text.LocalizedString: Huh? Who’s <NPCName>Charles</>?

Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to scare you, but you should keep those vitamins handy when you go into combat.

Text.LocalizedString: They help me recover instantly. Ask the doctors if you don’t believe me.

Text.SourceString: Well, yeah. They don’t taste good, but we don’t get them for the taste.//We take medicine to get better fast.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, yeah. They don’t taste good, but we don’t get them for the taste.//We take medicine to get better fast.

Text.SourceString: You sound like my son, <NPCName>Kenny</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You sound like my son, <NPCName>Kenny</>.

Text.SourceString: When he was seven.
Text.LocalizedString: When he was seven.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Jack</> needs extra help stocking the shelves. Not a hard job, just time consuming, that’s all.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Jack</> needs extra help stocking the shelves. Not a hard job, just time consuming, that’s all.

Text.SourceString: If you need anything, you should talk to <NPCName>Jack</>. I don’t know much about selling these.
Text.LocalizedString: If you need anything, you should talk to <NPCName>Jack</>. I don’t know much about selling these.

Text.SourceString: How’s the old cabin? Holding up okay?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s the old cabin? Holding up okay?

Text.SourceString: The house?//<portrait=normal>Oh, the cabin, you mean? There are some people from the Band of Smiles in the guildhouse.
Text.LocalizedString: The house?//<portrait=normal>Oh, the cabin, you mean? There are some people from the Band of Smiles in the guildhouse.

Text.SourceString: I don’t really care about birthdays or parties in general.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really care about birthdays or parties in general.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, they’re all right. Some people make such a big deal out of it.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, they’re all right. Some people make such a big deal out of it.

Text.SourceString: Gah. You’re one of those <Italic>chipper</> ones.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah. You’re one of those <Italic>chipper</> ones.

Special.SourceString: I don’t mind. Birthdays are kind of fun.
Special.LocalizedString: I don’t mind. Birthdays are kind of fun.

Text.SourceString: It can be any date I want it to be.//What’s with the personal questions?
Text.LocalizedString: It can be any date I want it to be.//What’s with the personal questions?

Text.SourceString: It isn’t listed. I don’t celebrate it.//Personal reasons.
Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t listed. I don’t celebrate it.//Personal reasons.

Special.SourceString: I don’t remember seeing your birthday on the calendar.
Special.LocalizedString: I don’t remember seeing your birthday on the calendar.

Text.SourceString: Playing the flute used to keep me entertained when I was alone in the caves for days.
Text.LocalizedString: Playing the flute used to keep me entertained when I was alone in the caves for days.

Text.SourceString: It calmed me down.//There’s not much else to do down there.//<portrait=annoyed>In the cavern, I mean.
Text.LocalizedString: It calmed me down.//There’s not much else to do down there.//<portrait=annoyed>In the cavern, I mean.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ben</> sometimes brings me fresh flowers. He charges for them, yeah. Not much, though.//Friends and family price, he says.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ben</> sometimes brings me fresh flowers. He charges for them, yeah. Not much, though.//Friends and family price, he says.

Text.SourceString: Did you go to the cavern at all last week?//<portrait=annoyed>Why am I asking?//<portrait=normal>It’s my job to know everything that goes on in there.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you go to the cavern at all last week?//<portrait=annoyed>Why am I asking?//<portrait=normal>It’s my job to know everything that goes on in there.

Text.SourceString: I like TV. You can kill so much time watching it.
Text.LocalizedString: I like TV. You can kill so much time watching it.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like the sun. It’s always so bright.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like the sun. It’s always so bright.

Text.SourceString: It’s blinding.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s blinding.

Text.SourceString: Unfortunately, we still get visitors even though we live deep in the woods.//Unwanted visitors.
Text.LocalizedString: Unfortunately, we still get visitors even though we live deep in the woods.//Unwanted visitors.

Text.SourceString: You’re worse than that wine lady down the hill, always visiting and bringing baskets of things.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re worse than that wine lady down the hill, always visiting and bringing baskets of things.

Text.SourceString: The swords and armor are getting rusty. What a sad sight.//Starting to show their age.
Text.LocalizedString: The swords and armor are getting rusty. What a sad sight.//Starting to show their age.

Text.SourceString: They still work fine.//A little cleaning and they’ll be brand new again.
Text.LocalizedString: They still work fine.//A little cleaning and they’ll be brand new again.

Text.SourceString: I can smell the ocean all the way from here.
Text.LocalizedString: I can smell the ocean all the way from here.

Text.SourceString: You just can’t escape the ocean here, can ya?
Text.LocalizedString: You just can’t escape the ocean here, can ya?

Text.SourceString: I’d rather live in the forest. I don’t really like talking to people.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d rather live in the forest. I don’t really like talking to people.

Text.SourceString: I’m not much of a people person.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not much of a people person.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like it when people stare.//Eye contact – ugh. But it’s rude not to look people in the eye, so I just limit my social life in general.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like it when people stare.//Eye contact – ugh. But it’s rude not to look people in the eye, so I just limit my social life in general.

Text.SourceString: The B.O.S. hunters are different. They don’t need social norms.//You could be in the same room with them all day and completely ignore them. They wouldn’t think anything of it.//They’re easy to be around.
Text.LocalizedString: The B.O.S. hunters are different. They don’t need social norms.//You could be in the same room with them all day and completely ignore them. They wouldn’t think anything of it.//They’re easy to be around.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to tell how safe the cavern is anymore.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to make a big deal about it, but I sure hope somebody carries on my legacy and protects this island.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to tell how safe the cavern is anymore.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to make a big deal about it, but I sure hope somebody carries on my legacy and protects this island.

Text.SourceString: We all know <NPCName>Kenny</> won’t do it. He wouldn’t hurt a fly.
Text.LocalizedString: We all know <NPCName>Kenny</> won’t do it. He wouldn’t hurt a fly.

Text.SourceString: Combat is about being quick on your feet and thinking on the go.
Text.LocalizedString: Combat is about being quick on your feet and thinking on the go.

Text.SourceString: You want to win, you need your footwork.//No way around it.
Text.LocalizedString: You want to win, you need your footwork.//No way around it.

Text.SourceString: “Wash your hands.” Pfft!//What’re my dirty hands going to do, kill me? Ha ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: “Wash your hands.” Pfft!//What’re my dirty hands going to do, kill me? Ha ha ha!

Text.SourceString: You sound like my son, <NPCName>Kenny</>.//<portrait=happy>When he was seven.
Text.LocalizedString: You sound like my son, <NPCName>Kenny</>.//<portrait=happy>When he was seven.

Text.SourceString: Timing is crucial in combat.//You don’t need maximum strength if your timing is impeccable.
Text.LocalizedString: Timing is crucial in combat.//You don’t need maximum strength if your timing is impeccable.

Text.SourceString: You need to know when to attack and when to duck.//And when to run away.
Text.LocalizedString: You need to know when to attack and when to duck.//And when to run away.

Text.SourceString: Yoga’s good training for combat.//Core strength. That’s the key.
Text.LocalizedString: Yoga’s good training for combat.//Core strength. That’s the key.

Text.SourceString: Keep your head during combat.//When you panic, you lose.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep your head during combat.//When you panic, you lose.

Text.SourceString: If you’re defeated, run.//Try again tomorrow. No need to force it.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes we lose. That’s just how it is with everything.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re defeated, run.//Try again tomorrow. No need to force it.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes we lose. That’s just how it is with everything.

Text.SourceString: It’s easier to grow your own food than going to Starlet to buy it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s easier to grow your own food than going to Starlet to buy it.

Text.SourceString: How much is a sack of potatoes going for these days?//I might sell some of my harvest. Planted way too much.
Text.LocalizedString: How much is a sack of potatoes going for these days?//I might sell some of my harvest. Planted way too much.

Text.SourceString: How much is a pumpkin going for these days?//I might sell some of mine. Planted way too much.
Text.LocalizedString: How much is a pumpkin going for these days?//I might sell some of mine. Planted way too much.

Text.SourceString: Living in the forest has taught me to respect nature.
Text.LocalizedString: Living in the forest has taught me to respect nature.

Text.SourceString: We often hear things at night, all kinds of noises.//Nothing to worry about. It’s probably wild animals.
Text.LocalizedString: We often hear things at night, all kinds of noises.//Nothing to worry about. It’s probably wild animals.

Text.SourceString: Spring isn’t so bad here.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring isn’t so bad here.

Text.SourceString: Fall is breezy here.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is breezy here.

Text.SourceString: Winter is finally here.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is finally here.

Text.SourceString: Some traveling friends in the guild visit me sometimes.//They’re welcome for as long as they want to stay.
Text.LocalizedString: Some traveling friends in the guild visit me sometimes.//They’re welcome for as long as they want to stay.

Text.SourceString: I don’t provide food. My friends bring their own food when they visit.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t provide food. My friends bring their own food when they visit.

Text.SourceString: Don’t expect too much from me.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t expect too much from me.
